- **Title:** WO2025104236A1 - Composés pyrazole utilisés en tant que composés d'ubiquitine ligase cullin-ring (Google Patents)  
  **URL:** `https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2025104236A1/fr` ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2025104236A1/fr))  
  - “WO2025104236A1 PCT/EP2024/082478 EP2024082478W” ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2025104236A1/fr))  
  - “Small molecules may modulate E3 ligases and other components of the ubiquitin - proteasome pathway also by operating via a “molecular glue” type of mechanism.” ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2025104236A1/fr))  
  - “targeted degradation of certain proteins, namely in particular cyclin K (CONK) and/or CDK12 and/or CDK13.” ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2025104236A1/fr))  

- **Title:** The CDK12 inhibitor SR-4835 functions as a molecular glue that promotes cyclin K degradation in melanoma (PubMed)  
  **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38104154/` ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38104154/))  
  - “SR-4835 uniquely promotes cyclin K degradation via the proteasome.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38104154/?utm_source=openai))  
  - “SR-4835 acts as a molecular glue that recruits the CDK12-cyclin K complex to the CUL4-RBX1-DDB1 ubiquitin ligase complex” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38104154/))  
  - “The benzimidazole side-chain of SR-4835 modulates its molecular glue activity.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38104154/))  

- **Title:** Discovery and design of molecular glue enhancers of CDK12–DDB1 interactions for targeted degradation of cyclin K (RSC Chemical Biology)  
  **URL:** `https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2025/cb/d4cb00190g` ([pubs.rsc.org](https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2025/cb/d4cb00190g))  
  - “SR-4835 occupies the ATP-binding pocket of CDK12 and bridges the CDK12–DDB1 interface” ([pubs.rsc.org](https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2025/cb/d4cb00190g))  
  - “SR-4835 effectively degraded cyclin K (D _{max} > 95%) with a DC _{50} of approximately 90 nM” ([pubs.rsc.org](https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2025/cb/d4cb00190g))  
  - “we appended this motif onto a structurally similar CDK12/pan-CDK inhibitor, dinaciclib, to generate compound MR-1226” ([pubs.rsc.org](https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2025/cb/d4cb00190g))  

- **Title:** Emerging approaches to CDK inhibitor development, a structural perspective (RSC Chemical Biology)  
  **URL:** `https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2023/cb/d2cb00201a` ([pubs.rsc.org](https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2023/cb/d2cb00201a))  
  - “Current molecular glues against CDKs are limited to CDK12, CDK13, and CDK4.” ([pubs.rsc.org](https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2023/cb/d2cb00201a))  
  - “HQ461 mediates the degradation of cyclin K by interacting with CDK12-cyclin K and the DDB1-CUL4-RBX1 E3 ligase complex.” ([pubs.rsc.org](https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2023/cb/d2cb00201a))  
  - “analogues HQ014 and HQ015” ([pubs.rsc.org](https://pubs.rsc.org/en/content/articlehtml/2023/cb/d2cb00201a))  

- **Title:** Noncovalent CDK12/13 dual inhibitors-based PROTACs degrade CDK12-Cyclin K complex and induce synthetic lethality with PARP inhibitor (PubMed)  
  **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/` ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))  
  - “we have synthesized a potent PROTAC degrader PP-C8” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))  
  - “PP-C8 demonstrates profound synergistic antiproliferative effects with PARP inhibitor in triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC).” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))  

- **Title:** WO2020219650A1 - Degraders of cyclin-dependent kinase 12 (cdk12) and uses thereof (Google Patents)  
  **URL:** `https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2020219650A1/zh` ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2020219650A1/zh))  
  - “WO2020219650A1 PCT/US2020/029483 US2020029483W” ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2020219650A1/zh))  
  - “PROTAC proteolysis targeting chimeras” ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2020219650A1/zh))  
  - “cancers (e.g., ovarian cancer, breast cancer, or prostate cancer)) associated with the target protein (e.g., kinase (e.g., CDK (e.g., CDK9, CDK12)))” ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2020219650A1/zh))  

- **Title:** US20240368147A1 - Cyclin k degrader (Google Patents)  
  **URL:** `https://patents.google.com/patent/US20240368147A1/en` ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/US20240368147A1/en))  
  - “US20240368147A1 US18/686,748” ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/US20240368147A1/en))  
  - “protein degron can be divided into three categories, namely proteolysis targeting chimera (PROTAC), monovalent degron and molecular glue degron” ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/US20240368147A1/en))  
  - “the CDK inhibitor CR8 induces the degradation of Cyclin K protein through the mechanism of a molecular glue degrader.” ([patents.google.com](https://patents.google.com/patent/US20240368147A1/en))
